      "results": [
        {
          "properties": {
            "tags": [
              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE:HIGH",
              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE_REASON:Source: `strength.getFeedback().getSuggestions()` which is derived from user-controlled input (`password`). Sink: Line 73, `output.append(\"\u003cli\u003e\" + sug + \"\u003c/li\u003e\")`. Dataflow: The `sug` variable, which comes from `strength.getFeedback().getSuggestions()`, is directly concatenated into the HTML output. Sanitization: No sanitization is applied. Conclusion: The lack of sanitization for user-controlled suggestions leads to a reflected XSS vulnerability as HTML/JavaScript can be injected into the list items rendered in the browser."
            ]
          },
          "ruleId": "datadog/java-xss",
          "ruleIndex": 7,
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Source: `strength.getFeedback().getSuggestions()` which is derived from user-controlled input (`password`). Sink: Line 73, `output.append(\"\u003cli\u003e\" + sug + \"\u003c/li\u003e\")`. Dataflow: The `sug` variable, which comes from `strength.getFeedback().getSuggestions()`, is directly concatenated into the HTML output. Sanitization: No sanitization is applied. Conclusion: The lack of sanitization for user-controlled suggestions leads to a reflected XSS vulnerability as HTML/JavaScript can be injected into the list items rendered in the browser."
          },
