              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE_REASON:Source: The `strength.getFeedback().getWarning()` method returns user-controlled feedback. Sink: The `output.append()` at line 67 directly concatenates this untrusted string into the HTML output. Dataflow: The user-controlled warning message flows directly from the `getWarning()` method to the `output.append()` call. Sanitization: No sanitization or encoding is applied to the warning message before it is embedded in the HTML. If the warning contains HTML or JavaScript, it will lead to XSS. Conclusion: This is a confirmed XSS vulnerability."
            ]
          },
          "ruleId": "datadog/java-xss",
