              "DATADOG_CONFIDENCE_REASON:Source: The `id` parameter from `request.getParameter(\"id\")` at line 99 is user-controlled.\n\nSink: The `id` parameter is unsafely used to construct a file path in `new File(catPicturesDirectory, (id == null ? RandomUtils.nextInt(1, 11) : id) + \".jpg\")` at line 101.\n\nDataflow: The user-controlled `id` flows directly into the file path construction.\n\nSanitization: The initial `queryParams` check at lines 93-95 is insufficient because `request.getParameter(\"id\")` is retrieved later, allowing an attacker to bypass this check and inject path traversal sequences into the `id` parameter directly. The vulnerability lies in the fact that the check is performed on `queryParams` and not directly on the `id` parameter used in the file path construction.\n\nConclusion: This is a confirmed Path Traversal vulnerability."
